NAME
	nsh - minimal shell

SYNOPSIS
	nsh [script]
Script:
	run testscript to test nsh


DESCRIPTION
	Minimal shell that mimics some features of sh. 

	Extensions Implemented:

		1. Allow meta characters to appear without spaces around them
		2. Single Quoting
		3. Multiple Pipes
		4. Environment Variables

	Regular Features:

		      CD [directory] - Change to specified directory or HOME if none are given	
		
			      Ctrl-D - Exit the shell

	Script [option]... [file]... - Execute a script or program

	    Script | Script | Script - Pipe scripts
	
       Script < [infile] > [outfile] - Input Output Redirection
